WEBVTT

00:17.159 --> 00:26.793
♪♪

00:26.828 --> 00:36.473
♪♪

00:36.508 --> 00:45.581
♪♪

00:47.013 --> 00:56.988
♪♪

01:00.092 --> 01:10.067
♪♪

01:10.102 --> 01:20.077
♪♪

01:20.112 --> 01:30.087
♪♪

01:30.122 --> 01:40.097
♪♪

01:42.739 --> 01:52.714
♪♪

01:52.749 --> 02:01.624
♪♪

02:12.835 --> 02:18.938
♪♪

02:21.173 --> 02:29.047
♪♪

02:29.082 --> 02:30.884
-David Stevens?
-Yeah.

02:32.118 --> 02:41.895
♪♪

02:46.308 --> 02:48.968
You from Riga?
It's my first time.

02:49.003 --> 02:54.138
Love the, uh, the architecture.
It's so beautiful here.

02:54.173 --> 03:03.620
♪♪

03:08.022 --> 03:17.997
♪♪

03:18.032 --> 03:24.839
♪♪

03:27.173 --> 03:34.684
♪♪

03:34.719 --> 03:36.455
-Good to see you,

03:36.490 --> 03:37.720
you old rattlesnake.
-Ohh!

03:37.755 --> 03:39.326
-David, how you doing?
-Grant!

03:39.361 --> 03:41.119
-Good. How was your flight, man?

03:41.154 --> 03:43.660
-Oh, it was good.
-Good!

03:43.695 --> 03:47.532
So the, uh, painters are
behind on your apartment,

03:47.567 --> 03:49.996
but they assure me
they'll be out in a few weeks,

03:50.031 --> 03:52.405
and then we can get you
closer to town.

03:52.440 --> 03:54.671
-No, it's -- it's fine.
Really, Grant.

03:54.706 --> 03:57.575
-But it still needs
a lot of work, the exterior.

03:57.610 --> 04:00.204
-I think it's --
I think it's beautiful, really.

04:00.239 --> 04:02.415
I like it.
-Good. Well, the office

04:02.450 --> 04:04.384
is walkable from the train,

04:04.419 --> 04:07.244
and there's a train station
very close by.

04:07.279 --> 04:09.719
Or else you could use
my other car,

04:09.754 --> 04:13.019
which is in the, uh, garage,
if you need to.

04:13.054 --> 04:14.856
You'll get the lay of the land.

04:14.891 --> 04:16.363
-You know, I just want to say
thank you

04:16.398 --> 04:17.859
for setting this up, Grant,
really.

04:17.894 --> 04:20.532
It's -- I'm excited for
some change, you know?

04:20.567 --> 04:22.600
-Well, don't be too excited.

04:22.635 --> 04:25.372
I need you to serve
as a swing writer.

04:25.407 --> 04:27.341
I know it's a step down
for you now,

04:27.376 --> 04:29.200
but, uh, we'll get you
into the system,

04:29.235 --> 04:31.235
and we'll go from there.
-Okay. That's --

04:31.270 --> 04:33.578
Yeah, that's no problem.
I'm here to work.

04:33.613 --> 04:36.240
You know me.
Alright.

04:36.275 --> 04:46.085
♪♪

04:46.120 --> 04:55.930
♪♪

04:55.965 --> 04:58.504
♪♪

05:15.017 --> 05:17.820
Excuse me. Sorry, I'm lost.

05:17.855 --> 05:19.987
Hi. I'm David.
-David Stevens.

05:23.630 --> 05:26.026
-Uh...

05:28.701 --> 05:31.328
-Your desk is over there.

05:31.363 --> 05:33.638
-Thank you.

05:35.972 --> 05:38.610
-Hi.
-Hi.

05:42.682 --> 05:45.144
Hey, how you doing, man?
-Good.

05:45.179 --> 05:47.421
-Yeah? Alright.

05:47.456 --> 05:50.457
-So, you met Iris? Hmm?

05:50.492 --> 05:53.790
-Yeah, I did.
-She's amazing.

05:53.825 --> 05:55.858
I mean, if you're looking.

05:57.158 --> 05:59.257
Noted.

06:30.257 --> 06:32.158
Oh.

06:38.265 --> 06:40.331
Come on.

07:07.602 --> 07:09.261
-Hi.

07:09.296 --> 07:11.329
I'm sorry to bother you.
Um...

07:15.742 --> 07:17.676
-Hello. I'm Robert.

07:17.711 --> 07:19.040
-Oh, you're British.

07:19.075 --> 07:20.877
-Yeah, my mom was.
I went to school there.

07:20.912 --> 07:23.550
-Okay.
-And you're a hamster.

07:23.585 --> 07:25.684
-Is that what I said?

07:25.719 --> 07:28.720
-Yeah.

07:28.755 --> 07:30.590
How can I help you, David?

07:30.625 --> 07:32.218
-Uh, I can't seem to
get my car started.

07:32.253 --> 07:34.891
I was wondering if you had
a gas can that I could borrow.

07:34.926 --> 07:36.761
-Oh, I think I can do a little
bit better than that --

07:36.796 --> 07:38.125
give you some actual gas.

07:38.160 --> 07:40.391
Come in.
-Oh. That's amazing. Thank you.

07:40.426 --> 07:42.228
-Excuse the mess.

07:42.263 --> 07:45.902
Do you want a beer or something?
-Oh, no. Maybe another time.

07:45.937 --> 07:48.542
I just really want to
get the car sorted.

07:48.577 --> 07:50.467
-Right.

08:03.955 --> 08:05.383
-Here you go.

08:05.418 --> 08:07.286
-Alright. Thank you.

08:07.321 --> 08:08.892
Did you catch that?

08:08.927 --> 08:11.092
-Yes, I did.
-Huh.

08:11.127 --> 08:13.127
-You fish?
-Oh, no.

08:13.162 --> 08:16.064
As a kid, uh,
I wasn't very good at it.

08:16.099 --> 08:18.297
Okay, uh, thank you...
-Welcome.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.672
-...for this.

08:19.707 --> 08:22.576
Look, I will return this
full tomorrow, I promise.

08:22.611 --> 08:25.678
-No problem.
I know where you live.

08:25.713 --> 08:28.549
-Right?

08:39.221 --> 08:41.452
Come on, you piece of shit.

08:47.526 --> 08:50.428
Alright.

08:50.463 --> 08:52.133
What the fuck?

08:56.469 --> 08:58.172
David, do you need a hand?

08:58.207 --> 09:00.471
Hey. Um...

09:00.506 --> 09:02.176
Yeah.

09:04.048 --> 09:07.148
-The fuse box is good.
-Mm-hmm.

09:07.183 --> 09:09.656
Are you a mechanic?

09:09.691 --> 09:11.152
-Me?
-Yeah.

09:11.187 --> 09:12.483
-I'm a nurse.

09:12.518 --> 09:14.826
I work for
a mobile nursing unit.

09:14.861 --> 09:17.961
-Wow, that sounds rewarding
-It's an odd job, really.

09:17.996 --> 09:21.800
A lot of people come to Riga
to die. It's nice like that.

09:21.835 --> 09:24.462
What about you?
-I'm a journalist, yeah.

09:24.497 --> 09:26.530
-Oh, really?
-Mm-hmm.

09:26.565 --> 09:28.235
-Have you written
anything I've read?

09:28.270 --> 09:31.678
-No, probably not.
Just mostly U.S. news.

09:31.713 --> 09:35.506
-Okay.
Try it now.

09:36.751 --> 09:38.685
-Take it for a ride,

09:38.720 --> 09:42.051
let the gas go through.
-Yeah.

09:42.086 --> 09:44.152
Hey, uh, I'm not really good
with cars.

09:44.187 --> 09:46.825
You want to go for a spin in
case this bad boy breaks down?

09:46.860 --> 09:49.322
-Alright.

09:49.357 --> 09:58.870
♪♪

10:03.371 --> 10:05.206
Car sounds good.

10:05.241 --> 10:07.340
-Mm-hmm.

10:07.375 --> 10:09.210
-So did you come here alone?

10:09.245 --> 10:10.915
-Yeah, just me.

10:10.950 --> 10:12.543
-No wife, no girlfriend,
nothing?

10:12.578 --> 10:15.381
-Nah.

10:15.416 --> 10:16.723
No, we're done, you know?

10:16.758 --> 10:18.285
It's kind of the reason
why I'm here.

10:18.320 --> 10:20.925
-I'm sorry. Fuck.
-No, that's alright.

10:20.960 --> 10:23.895
-Yeah, she...

10:23.930 --> 10:26.799
She dumped me because
I wasn't ready to get married,

10:26.834 --> 10:30.297
and then she ran off
with my best friend.

10:30.332 --> 10:33.564
-I don't think
he was your<i> best</i> friend.

10:33.599 --> 10:36.633
Yeah, I guess not.

10:36.668 --> 10:41.077
-You know, from suffering
comes happiness.

10:41.112 --> 10:44.080
You have to believe
you'll be alright.

10:44.115 --> 10:46.478
The universe will take care
of the rest.

10:46.513 --> 10:47.886
-Mm.

10:47.921 --> 10:51.582
-Or something. I mean,
what the fuck do I know?

10:52.860 --> 10:54.420
No, I like that, I like that.

10:54.455 --> 10:57.291
Hey, that's good. You know,
you're a good guy, man.

10:57.326 --> 11:02.098
♪♪

11:11.307 --> 11:14.440
♪♪

11:23.550 --> 11:25.957
-Come in.
-Hey.

11:25.992 --> 11:27.486
-Hey!
-So I'm going to head out.

11:27.521 --> 11:30.797
Uh, I sent you that
money laundering piece.

11:30.832 --> 11:32.799
-Great. Great.
I-I'll have a look.

11:32.834 --> 11:34.625
-Okay, cool.

11:34.660 --> 11:39.630
Hey, uh, if you're up for it
later, drinks, my treat.

11:39.665 --> 11:42.270
-Oh, shit. I'm sorry,
I would love to,

11:42.305 --> 11:45.207
but I got this, uh,
phone interview from Boston.

11:45.242 --> 11:48.045
It's probably going to go late.
-Okay. Sure. It's no problem.

11:48.080 --> 11:50.476
-Take a rain check.
-Yeah.

11:50.511 --> 11:52.346
See you tomorrow.

11:52.381 --> 11:54.315
<i>-...Pieces of leaves</i>
<i>with their jaws.</i>

11:54.350 --> 11:57.285
<i>The are</i>
<i>transported back to the nest,</i>

11:57.320 --> 12:00.486
<i>where they are processed</i>
<i>into a nutritional substrate</i>

12:00.521 --> 12:03.797
<i>for their subterranean</i>
<i>fungus gardens.</i>

12:03.832 --> 12:07.328
<i>It's this symbiosis between</i>
<i>the ants and the fungus</i>

12:07.363 --> 12:11.838
<i>that appears to be rewriting</i>
<i>the insect evolution.</i>

12:11.873 --> 12:13.730
<i>But we still don't...</i>

12:22.378 --> 12:27.678
♪♪

12:29.583 --> 12:31.187
-David.
-Hey.

12:31.222 --> 12:33.024
-Hey.
-What are you up to?

12:33.059 --> 12:34.894
-Watching TV.
-Yeah?

12:34.929 --> 12:36.588
You wanna go grab a drink?
-Now?

12:36.623 --> 12:39.360
-Yeah, I owe you a drink for
helping me with the car, so...

12:39.395 --> 12:41.692
-Alright.

12:41.727 --> 12:44.365
I'll throw something on.
-Okay.

12:53.915 --> 13:00.744
♪♪

13:03.419 --> 13:11.392
♪♪

13:11.427 --> 13:13.064
-To the universe.

13:13.099 --> 13:15.627
-Yeah, the universe.

13:17.763 --> 13:21.237
Hey, listen, I've read
a couple of your articles.

13:21.272 --> 13:23.910
You write well.
-Thank you.

13:23.945 --> 13:26.044
Thank you for reading.
-Yeah.

13:26.079 --> 13:28.574
Doesn't make you feel good?
-No.

13:28.609 --> 13:30.708
-Cheers.

13:32.844 --> 13:35.614
♪♪

13:37.816 --> 13:47.758
♪♪

13:47.793 --> 13:57.471
♪♪

13:57.506 --> 14:00.980
-I'll have another one.
Thank you.

14:03.875 --> 14:06.480
I'd like a drink.
What is it?

14:07.516 --> 14:10.814
-It's called
a short trip to hell.

14:10.849 --> 14:13.784
Short trip to --
I like the sound of that.

14:13.819 --> 14:16.325
-Want a sip?

14:19.033 --> 14:22.595
One's good, but the second,
you might regret it.

14:22.630 --> 14:25.301
-Well, I'll buy the next round,
then.

14:25.336 --> 14:28.436
-This is my...third, I think.

14:30.407 --> 14:31.703
I'm David.

14:31.738 --> 14:33.870
-Janine.
-Janine?

14:33.905 --> 14:35.806
I like your bracelet, Janine.

14:35.841 --> 14:38.644
-That? Just my cycling ID.

14:38.679 --> 14:40.613
-What?
-It's for my bike.

14:40.648 --> 14:42.021
I cycle everywhere.

14:42.056 --> 14:45.222
It's got emergency contacts
and stuff.

14:45.257 --> 14:47.389
American?

14:48.392 --> 14:50.293
-Mm-hmm.

14:50.328 --> 14:53.131
I'm just here for work.
What brings you to Riga?

14:53.166 --> 14:55.034
-Soul searching.
-Ah, soul.

14:55.069 --> 14:58.004
-I'm from London originally.

14:58.039 --> 15:00.468
-Um, are you with anyone?

15:00.503 --> 15:03.042
-I met some friends earlier,
but they've gone.

15:03.077 --> 15:05.539
What about you?
-Yeah.

15:08.247 --> 15:11.017
A friend. He's here somewhere.
-Yeah, sure.

15:11.052 --> 15:13.910
You don't have to make things
up. You're better than that.

15:13.945 --> 15:16.583
-I'm not. I'm not.
-Convince me.

15:16.618 --> 15:18.420
Come on.

15:18.455 --> 15:28.430
♪♪

15:28.465 --> 15:38.440
♪♪

15:38.475 --> 15:48.450
♪♪

15:48.485 --> 15:58.460
♪♪

15:58.495 --> 16:08.470
♪♪

16:08.505 --> 16:17.743
♪♪

16:17.778 --> 16:20.086
You've got my number. Call me.

16:20.121 --> 16:23.452
-I'll buy you another drink --
water, anything.

16:23.487 --> 16:27.654
-Another time. I have to get up
early in the morning for work.

16:29.130 --> 16:30.954
-Don't go.

16:33.926 --> 16:36.135
-Yes?

16:36.170 --> 16:37.730
-Now you got my number.

16:37.765 --> 16:39.831
-Right.

16:39.866 --> 16:44.803
♪♪

16:44.838 --> 16:47.509
-Uh, yes.

16:47.544 --> 16:50.611
-I'm sorry to leave you hanging.

16:50.646 --> 16:53.284
I just met
the most amazing girl.

16:53.319 --> 16:54.450
-Oh, yeah?
-Yeah.

16:54.485 --> 16:55.847
-Did you get her number?
-I did.

16:55.882 --> 16:57.948
-Good. Let's go.

17:06.200 --> 17:09.135
Do you want to go for
another beer or something?

17:09.170 --> 17:11.027
-I got to work tomorrow.
I wish I could.

17:25.351 --> 17:27.318
I don't think you should smoke
in this car.

17:27.353 --> 17:30.156
-I'm sorry, man.
-No, it's all good. Here.

17:32.160 --> 17:34.358
Alright.

17:36.230 --> 17:37.823
-Mm.

17:37.858 --> 17:39.660
-Do you know how to work this?

17:39.695 --> 17:42.531
-No, that's the wrong button.
Oh, shit.

17:44.898 --> 17:46.062
-Watch out!

17:54.039 --> 17:56.677
-David, we hit something.

17:56.712 --> 17:58.745
-What?

18:04.720 --> 18:07.017
♪♪

18:08.460 --> 18:11.164
♪♪

18:13.894 --> 18:22.703
♪♪

18:22.738 --> 18:24.100
-Shit.

18:24.135 --> 18:26.212
J-Janine?

18:26.247 --> 18:28.874
Janine? What the fuck?

18:28.909 --> 18:31.283
What the fuck?

18:32.748 --> 18:35.254
-Move away.

18:37.588 --> 18:38.752
-Robert?

18:38.787 --> 18:40.820
-She's not breathing.

18:44.991 --> 18:48.894
♪♪

18:48.929 --> 18:51.303
Ooh, come on. Come on.

18:51.338 --> 18:54.240
-Robert, what's wrong with her?
-Come on, babe.

18:58.939 --> 19:06.912
♪♪

19:06.947 --> 19:14.755
♪♪

19:14.790 --> 19:18.594
She's dead, David.
-Shit. Shit.

19:18.629 --> 19:20.563
Shit, shit.

19:20.598 --> 19:22.928
-David, I'm sorry, mate.
-Oh!

19:22.963 --> 19:24.765
Shit!
-David, David...

19:24.800 --> 19:27.966
David, I'm sorry, David.
-Oh, God. Fuck. Oh, God.

19:28.001 --> 19:30.672
Oh, God, it can't be.

19:30.707 --> 19:32.608
She can't be dead.

19:32.643 --> 19:35.809
Why are you driving your bike
down the middle of the road?

19:35.844 --> 19:39.010
Why is there
no fucking bike path?!

19:39.045 --> 19:40.286
Please.

19:40.321 --> 19:43.113
Why don't you just wake up?
Wake up.

19:43.148 --> 19:45.489
-David, we need to leave now.

19:45.524 --> 19:48.624
-We got to call for help.
-We can't call anybody.

19:48.659 --> 19:52.089
You've been drinking.
This is murder.

19:54.995 --> 19:57.127
David, we have to go.

19:57.162 --> 19:59.635
Now, David!

19:59.670 --> 20:02.341
♪♪

20:02.376 --> 20:04.607
-Oh, fuck.

20:06.545 --> 20:08.138
-David!

20:08.173 --> 20:09.348
-I'm sorry.

20:09.383 --> 20:11.317
I'm so sorry.

20:13.178 --> 20:15.552
I'm sorry.

20:15.587 --> 20:19.886
♪♪

20:26.697 --> 20:35.572
♪♪

21:11.412 --> 21:13.874
We should have
called the police.

21:13.909 --> 21:17.944
-This could have happened
to anyone.

21:17.979 --> 21:20.276
-Yeah.

21:21.884 --> 21:24.049
But it didn't.

21:24.084 --> 21:27.019
It happened to me.

21:27.054 --> 21:30.220
And it happened to her.

21:30.255 --> 21:33.630
-It happened to us, David.

21:33.665 --> 21:36.193
Look...

21:36.228 --> 21:38.866
I know this girl shouldn't have
been riding her bike in the dark

21:38.901 --> 21:40.571
with no light on.

21:40.606 --> 21:42.474
But if you report this,

21:42.509 --> 21:44.938
nothing's going to change
for that girl.

21:44.973 --> 21:47.270
You can't undo it.

21:47.305 --> 21:50.306
But what you<i> can</i> do is move on.

21:50.341 --> 21:53.914
What's past is past.

21:53.949 --> 21:56.620
Don't let this ruin us.

21:58.316 --> 21:59.788
Alright?

22:02.793 --> 22:04.925
Relax.

22:04.960 --> 22:08.258
♪♪

22:11.439 --> 22:21.447
♪♪

22:28.819 --> 22:35.252
♪♪

22:35.287 --> 22:45.262
♪♪

22:45.297 --> 22:52.302
♪♪

22:53.910 --> 22:56.878
♪♪

23:10.025 --> 23:14.192
♪♪

23:29.044 --> 23:39.019
♪♪

23:39.054 --> 23:45.927
♪♪

26:04.397 --> 26:14.372
♪♪

26:14.407 --> 26:16.341
-So where are we?

26:16.376 --> 26:19.751
-Okay.

26:19.786 --> 26:22.149
-Right. Kiel?

26:22.184 --> 26:25.482
-Yes. Police have concluded
the investigation

26:25.517 --> 26:27.693
into the murder of...

26:27.728 --> 26:31.587
♪♪

26:31.622 --> 26:35.701
-Okay. That, uh, leaves us
with the hit-and-run yesterday.

26:35.736 --> 26:38.594
Cyclist found dead.

26:38.629 --> 26:41.234
Uh, David, that would be you.

26:41.269 --> 26:43.709
Any questions?

26:43.744 --> 26:46.569
-Great. Let's get started.

26:46.604 --> 26:48.439
Happy Friday.

26:48.474 --> 26:51.244
-Thank you.

27:20.308 --> 27:26.114
♪♪

27:39.129 --> 27:48.972
♪♪

28:12.294 --> 28:22.203
♪♪

28:22.238 --> 28:32.213
♪♪

28:32.248 --> 28:41.585
♪♪

28:53.566 --> 28:59.141
♪♪

28:59.176 --> 29:06.445
♪♪

29:16.292 --> 29:18.589
Ohh!

29:37.313 --> 29:38.576
-Hey!

29:38.611 --> 29:41.447
You speak English?

29:42.923 --> 29:44.384
-Yes.

29:44.419 --> 29:47.552
-You were at
the press conference.

29:47.587 --> 29:51.061
-I'm one of the journalists.

29:51.096 --> 29:53.789
-They're saying
they have no leads.

29:53.824 --> 29:56.561
I-I don't understand.

29:56.596 --> 29:59.168
-Did you know her?

30:01.601 --> 30:03.942
-She's my sister.

30:03.977 --> 30:06.637
I'm not even meant
to be here yet.

30:06.672 --> 30:08.474
We -- We have kayaking.

30:08.509 --> 30:12.049
-I'm sorry. I have to go back --
back to the office.

30:12.084 --> 30:15.921
-Hey! Will you write...

30:15.956 --> 30:17.450
in -- in your article,
will you write

30:17.485 --> 30:20.959
that we need witnesses
to come forward?

30:23.931 --> 30:33.906
♪♪

30:33.941 --> 30:43.916
♪♪

30:43.951 --> 30:52.650
♪♪

30:52.685 --> 30:55.818
-You did what?!
-I took care of our problem.

30:55.853 --> 30:57.688
-And what did you do with it?

30:57.723 --> 31:00.625
-Do you really want to know?

31:00.660 --> 31:03.529
It's gone...for good.

31:05.533 --> 31:08.105
-I was at the police station
for the news conference.

31:08.140 --> 31:10.635
-Uh-huh.
-The girl's sister was there.

31:10.670 --> 31:13.044
-Whose sister?

31:13.079 --> 31:15.343
Who do you think?

31:15.378 --> 31:17.807
Janine's sister.

31:17.842 --> 31:20.018
She wants to know what happened.

31:20.053 --> 31:22.515
-Of course she does.

31:22.550 --> 31:24.517
What do the police know?

31:24.552 --> 31:26.651
-Nothing...

31:26.686 --> 31:29.720
far as I can tell, for now.

31:29.755 --> 31:31.458
-Good.

31:33.066 --> 31:35.528
-Robert?
-David?

31:37.367 --> 31:41.666
-It's not too late
to turn ourselves in.

31:41.701 --> 31:43.668
-Yes, it is.

31:45.375 --> 31:47.540
Do you know how many years
you'll get for a hit-and-run

31:47.575 --> 31:50.180
in Latvia?

31:50.215 --> 31:53.084
Do you want to go to prison
here...

31:53.119 --> 31:55.812
as an American?

31:55.847 --> 31:58.023
I wouldn't.

32:02.755 --> 32:04.854
Goddamn it.

32:04.889 --> 32:07.692
What do we do about the car?

32:07.727 --> 32:10.101
-Wait 'til tomorrow
and report it stolen.

32:10.136 --> 32:13.434
Look suspicious
if you did anything else.

32:13.469 --> 32:15.271
-Shit.

32:23.083 --> 32:27.679
-That night,
you and I went into town.

32:27.714 --> 32:30.055
But we didn't drive.

32:30.090 --> 32:32.123
We went to a bar.

32:32.158 --> 32:34.587
We had a few drinks.

32:34.622 --> 32:37.095
We left the bar at- 15

32:37.130 --> 32:40.626
and took a tram at- 30.

32:40.661 --> 32:42.892
Remember?

32:42.927 --> 32:45.631
Got it?

32:45.666 --> 32:47.402
Good.

32:47.437 --> 32:51.208
We have to protect each other.

32:51.243 --> 32:55.344
We have to rely on each other.

32:57.612 --> 33:03.946
♪♪

33:03.981 --> 33:10.557
♪♪

33:10.592 --> 33:12.757
Come on.

33:12.792 --> 33:14.594
It's beautiful, isn't it?

33:14.629 --> 33:15.892
-Mm-hmm.

33:15.927 --> 33:19.995
♪♪

33:20.030 --> 33:21.304
-You ready?

33:21.339 --> 33:24.109
Let's get involved.

33:26.674 --> 33:36.418
♪♪

33:36.453 --> 33:38.585
Oh, st-stay calm.
-What do I do? What do I do?

33:38.620 --> 33:40.851
-Let him have the hook.
-Okay, okay, okay.

33:40.886 --> 33:43.293
Whoo!

33:43.328 --> 33:45.295
-Whoa!

33:45.330 --> 33:46.659
-Wow!

33:46.694 --> 33:48.760
-Bring it in, bring it in,
bring it in.

33:48.795 --> 33:50.861
Come on.
-You got it?

33:53.140 --> 33:55.833
-You are blessed.

33:58.068 --> 34:02.609
♪♪

34:02.644 --> 34:03.973
What are you doing?

34:04.008 --> 34:07.152
-Jamie Oliver trick.

34:07.187 --> 34:10.188
-Oh, yeah.

34:11.488 --> 34:14.225
-You want a drink?
-No, I've tea, thanks.

34:20.024 --> 34:23.201
Sorry about the smell.
-It's alright.

34:23.236 --> 34:24.829
-I'd have cooked it outside,

34:24.864 --> 34:27.370
but my barbecue's broken.

34:34.940 --> 34:37.545
-Do you collect these?

34:39.945 --> 34:42.077
-Excuse me.

34:42.112 --> 34:45.850
Please...don't do that.

34:45.885 --> 34:48.589
-Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't...

34:56.566 --> 34:59.204
-My mother used to
leave them for me.

34:59.239 --> 35:01.437
She went away.

35:01.472 --> 35:06.211
-W-What do you mean,
went away?

35:07.907 --> 35:11.711
-You got a drink? Let's eat.

35:11.746 --> 35:19.257
♪♪

35:24.660 --> 35:28.090
-Yes, Officer, that is correct,
I'm not the owner of the car.

35:28.994 --> 35:32.468
Okay, so he has to be the one
to report it was stolen.

35:32.503 --> 35:35.735
Okay. I will tell him.

35:35.770 --> 35:39.442
Thank you.
-David, you have a visitor.

35:41.171 --> 35:44.139
-Hi. Um,
I don't know if you remember me.

35:44.174 --> 35:46.218
I'm Janine Rafael's sister.

35:46.253 --> 35:48.220
-Yes. How can I help you?

35:48.255 --> 35:49.650
-I'm Vanessa.

35:49.685 --> 35:52.147
You wrote that article
about my sister,

35:52.182 --> 35:55.150
about how the police
have no leads.

35:55.185 --> 35:56.921
-Yes.

35:56.956 --> 35:59.429
-I wanted to speak to you.

35:59.464 --> 36:01.926
The police, they're not moving
very quickly, and, uh...

36:01.961 --> 36:06.766
-You know, I-I really
have a deadline to finish.

36:06.801 --> 36:08.405
-Um, okay.

36:08.440 --> 36:11.166
Uh, maybe a drink after work?

36:11.201 --> 36:13.839
-Um, my schedule
is pretty packed.

36:15.678 --> 36:19.845
-Look, I think I know
how to catch the killer.

36:20.947 --> 36:23.651
♪♪

36:23.686 --> 36:27.292
This is the highway
from Dzintari to Riga,

36:27.327 --> 36:29.492
which is the fastest route
from the club.

36:29.527 --> 36:32.957
And this is the back road
where my sister died.

36:32.992 --> 36:35.124
-Right.
-What if someone

36:35.159 --> 36:37.302
was deliberately
avoiding the highway?

36:37.337 --> 36:39.436
-You know, most people
have driving habits.

36:39.471 --> 36:41.130
A road they'll
take during the day

36:41.165 --> 36:44.199
they will also take at night.

36:44.234 --> 36:46.905
-What if they'd drunk too much?

36:48.678 --> 36:50.480
-Still could have been
coming from Dzintari

36:50.515 --> 36:52.449
taking the back roads.

36:52.484 --> 36:54.814
-But that's a much longer trip.
-Look, all I'm saying is

36:54.849 --> 36:59.687
that there are many reasons why
someone might take that road.

37:03.528 --> 37:06.364
-So you're not going to help me.

37:07.763 --> 37:11.666
-I'll do what I can. Look,
let the police do their job.

37:11.701 --> 37:15.197
You know,
these things take time.

37:16.233 --> 37:18.607
-Yeah.

37:22.580 --> 37:27.143
Is someone

37:27.178 --> 37:30.883
helping you through all this?

37:34.922 --> 37:37.824
-My dad died
when we were younger.

37:39.256 --> 37:42.763
And my mom died
a few years back.

37:45.196 --> 37:48.373
Janine was all I had.

37:51.477 --> 37:55.039
Look, please.

37:55.074 --> 37:58.350
I need answers.

37:58.385 --> 38:01.683
I don't know what else to do.

38:01.718 --> 38:06.248
♪♪

38:06.283 --> 38:09.086
-I'll see what I can do.

38:09.121 --> 38:14.696
♪♪

38:14.731 --> 38:16.291
-Sorry.

38:16.326 --> 38:17.897
Thank you.

38:17.932 --> 38:27.412
♪♪

38:27.447 --> 38:37.620
♪♪

38:44.321 --> 38:46.959
Alright.

38:51.031 --> 38:52.767
-Do you know what?

38:52.802 --> 38:55.836
The best fishing I've ever done
is in Ludza.

38:55.871 --> 38:59.136
I mean, it's beautiful. It's not
far from here, actually.

38:59.171 --> 39:02.480
Fish just hop out of the water.

39:03.978 --> 39:07.276
Do you know what? I think we
should go together, you and I,

39:07.311 --> 39:08.816
to Ludza.

39:08.851 --> 39:10.620
I've got a mate up there
who rent apartments.

39:10.655 --> 39:12.083
Not expensive or anything.

39:12.118 --> 39:14.657
-Oh, fuck!
-Shit.

39:14.692 --> 39:17.088
Let me have a look at it.

39:21.292 --> 39:23.028
-What are you doing?

39:23.063 --> 39:26.328
-I'm sucking out the infection.
-Stop it!

39:29.003 --> 39:30.838
-I'm sorry.

39:30.873 --> 39:33.511
There's Band-Aids in the box.

39:43.556 --> 39:47.118
Look, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

39:47.153 --> 39:49.659
-It's fine.

39:49.694 --> 39:51.892
-No, it's a problem.

39:51.927 --> 39:54.290
-Robert?
-What?

39:54.325 --> 39:57.832
-I have killed a woman.

39:57.867 --> 40:00.197
-Yes.

40:00.232 --> 40:03.068
But you of all people should
know how this world works.

40:03.103 --> 40:05.642
-What the hell
does that even mean?

40:05.677 --> 40:07.743
-You worked as a journalist
in New York.

40:07.778 --> 40:10.174
-And
-Bad things happen
to good people all the time.

40:10.209 --> 40:12.176
Get over it.
-How about you

40:12.211 --> 40:16.048
take care of your own shit,
and I'll take care of mine?

40:16.083 --> 40:18.215
-Okay.

40:18.250 --> 40:20.888
If I did that, you'd be in jail.

40:20.923 --> 40:28.423
♪♪

40:32.462 --> 40:40.237
♪♪

40:40.272 --> 40:48.047
♪♪

40:50.557 --> 40:55.384
♪♪

40:55.419 --> 40:58.354
-Okay, how --
how do you spell --
-You just need that,

40:58.389 --> 41:00.598
that...

41:00.633 --> 41:03.359
-David, you got a second?

41:03.394 --> 41:05.394
-Uh, yeah.

41:05.429 --> 41:08.903
-That's fine. I'll finish. Yeah.

41:08.938 --> 41:11.543
-So you're settling in?
-Mm-hmm, yeah.

41:11.578 --> 41:14.469
Well, I met the guy
who lives next door.

41:14.504 --> 41:16.548
-Oh.
-Do you know anything about him?

41:16.583 --> 41:17.747
-Rob -- Robert?
-Mm-Hmm.

41:17.782 --> 41:19.276
-Something like that?

41:19.311 --> 41:20.915
Oh, well, neighbors told me

41:20.950 --> 41:23.247
that his mother
was an airline stewardess,

41:23.282 --> 41:26.954
used to leave him alone
for weeks and weeks as a kid.

41:26.989 --> 41:29.055
He's an odd bird.

41:29.090 --> 41:30.991
But...

41:32.995 --> 41:35.930
Is everything alright?
-I'm -- I'm --

41:35.965 --> 41:37.965
Yeah, I'm good.
I'm just working.

41:38.000 --> 41:41.430
-Okay.
That's good to hear.

41:41.465 --> 41:45.269
By the way, I'm, uh, thinking
of taking off this weekend.

41:45.304 --> 41:49.108
I'm going to go to the Baltic
Pride Festival in Vilnius.

41:49.143 --> 41:53.178
Probably, uh, need to swap cars
so we can all fit.

41:53.213 --> 41:56.588
-Oh, shit. I forgot to --
to tell you.

41:56.623 --> 41:58.788
I've been having trouble
keeping the car running.

41:58.823 --> 42:00.790
I was going to call a mechanic,
have him come out,

42:00.825 --> 42:03.188
take a look at it.

42:03.223 --> 42:06.125
Uh, just, you know,
a little gift from me to you.

42:06.160 --> 42:08.028
Everything you've done,
you know?

42:08.063 --> 42:11.130
-Don't worry about it. I'll get
one of the boys to drive us all.

42:11.165 --> 42:13.033
No problem.
-Right. Whatever's easiest.

42:13.068 --> 42:15.332
You know?
-No. All good. Okay.

42:15.367 --> 42:16.806
-Alright.

42:16.841 --> 42:19.534
I'm good, by the way.

42:35.926 --> 42:42.062
♪♪

42:42.097 --> 42:48.233
♪♪

42:50.336 --> 42:58.947
♪♪

43:11.060 --> 43:13.192
-You got a new car?
-Hey.

43:13.227 --> 43:16.327
Yeah, it's just a rental.
-Nice.

43:17.737 --> 43:19.396
-And you got a new grill.

43:19.431 --> 43:21.530
-This is for you, actually.

43:21.565 --> 43:23.741
-For me?
-Yeah.

43:23.776 --> 43:26.040
-David...

43:26.075 --> 43:28.680
-I know your old one messed up,

43:28.715 --> 43:31.683
so I wanted to apologize
for the other day.

43:31.718 --> 43:34.851
-Oh, please, mate. Forget it.
I mean, I will take the grill.

43:34.886 --> 43:36.413
Can't believe you remembered.
-Yeah.

43:36.448 --> 43:39.218
How about we fire it up tonight
for dinner? Sound good?

43:39.253 --> 43:40.417
-Yeah.
-Yeah?

43:40.452 --> 43:41.759
-I'll fire it up about- 00.

43:41.794 --> 43:43.728
-Okay.
-Okay. Thanks, David.

43:43.763 --> 43:45.290
-You're welcome.
-Yeah.

43:45.325 --> 43:48.590
Wow. I can't believe
you bought me a present.

43:48.625 --> 43:56.906
♪♪

44:02.749 --> 44:03.979
-Hello?

44:04.014 --> 44:07.543
-Hi, Vanessa,
it's David Stevenson.

44:07.578 --> 44:09.314
-Hey.

44:09.349 --> 44:11.822
-Um...

44:11.857 --> 44:16.255
Just calling to see
how you were doing.

44:16.290 --> 44:18.928
-Well, good, actually.

44:18.963 --> 44:20.765
Detective Reine called.

44:20.800 --> 44:23.658
A witnesses just came forward.

44:26.135 --> 44:27.596
-Really?

44:27.631 --> 44:31.336
♪♪

44:31.371 --> 44:34.273
-David.
-Robert, listen.

44:35.947 --> 44:38.178
A witness came forward.

44:40.644 --> 44:44.448
Some old lady who lives
by the road called the police.

44:44.483 --> 44:46.483
-Have they been to see her yet?

44:46.518 --> 44:49.288
-No. I'm sure they will today.

44:49.323 --> 44:52.962
-Listen to me.
There's no need to panic.

44:52.997 --> 44:55.294
You find out what they know.

44:55.329 --> 44:57.736
I'm sure it's nothing.

45:00.631 --> 45:08.670
♪♪

45:08.705 --> 45:16.821
♪♪

46:23.153 --> 46:24.548
-Hey.

46:24.583 --> 46:27.419
Thanks for coming so quickly.

46:27.454 --> 46:28.717
Come in.

46:28.752 --> 46:30.994
Take a seat.

46:35.099 --> 46:38.562
So witness came forward.

46:38.597 --> 46:40.729
-Detective Reine is on her way.

46:40.764 --> 46:44.370
Maybe now they'll catch
the piece of shit who did this.

46:44.405 --> 46:47.076
I don't know how
people sleep at night.

46:51.412 --> 46:55.579
I'm sorry.
Can I get you a drink?

46:55.614 --> 46:57.548
-Yeah. Sure.

46:57.583 --> 46:59.022
-Okay.

47:16.602 --> 47:19.339
♪♪

47:19.374 --> 47:20.670
Hello?

47:20.705 --> 47:29.954
♪♪

47:29.989 --> 47:39.458
♪♪

47:39.493 --> 47:48.698
♪♪

47:48.733 --> 47:54.605
♪♪

47:54.640 --> 47:57.146
The witness...

47:57.181 --> 48:00.149
s-she had a heart attack.

48:00.184 --> 48:02.514
She didn't make it.

48:07.818 --> 48:13.393
♪♪

48:13.428 --> 48:15.824
-I'm so sorry.

48:19.005 --> 48:25.834
♪♪

48:31.215 --> 48:34.348
-David.
-You will not believe this.

48:34.383 --> 48:38.088
The old lady, the witness,
she had a heart attack.

48:38.123 --> 48:41.091
-Okay. That's good.

48:41.126 --> 48:44.094
You okay?
-Yeah, yeah, I'm good.

48:44.129 --> 48:46.525
-What time you coming over?

48:47.759 --> 48:49.528
-Um...

48:49.563 --> 48:52.729
Hey, I'm really sorry to do
this. I'm way behind at work.

48:52.764 --> 48:54.203
-Yeah, yeah, sure.

48:54.238 --> 48:56.667
Come over whenever you want.
Don't sweat it.

48:56.702 --> 49:00.473
-No, I'm not going to be able
to make it. I'm really sorry.

49:02.081 --> 49:03.608
-Are you sure?

49:03.643 --> 49:06.545
I've got a lot
of really nice food here.

49:06.580 --> 49:08.283
Be a shame to waste it.

49:08.318 --> 49:11.715
-I'm just, uh -- I got to
finish this -- this piece,

49:11.750 --> 49:13.420
and they pushed my deadline.

49:13.455 --> 49:15.686
So I'm stuck here all night,
really.

49:15.721 --> 49:18.095
-Yeah, yeah. Sure, sure.
Go, go, go, go.

49:18.130 --> 49:20.625
Do your job, mate.
Yeah, no problem.

49:20.660 --> 49:22.627
-I'm really sorry.
-See you later.

49:22.662 --> 49:24.761
-Bye.

49:24.796 --> 49:28.237
♪♪

49:32.771 --> 49:42.746
♪♪

49:45.091 --> 49:48.587
♪♪

49:49.821 --> 49:57.794
♪♪

49:57.829 --> 50:06.110
♪♪

50:13.944 --> 50:15.152
Hello.

50:15.187 --> 50:17.946
I'm looking for David.

50:17.981 --> 50:19.915
-David Stevens?

50:19.950 --> 50:21.290
-Yes.

50:21.325 --> 50:23.127
We were meant to have a barbecue
this evening,

50:23.162 --> 50:25.492
and he called me
and said he had to work late.

50:25.527 --> 50:27.428
So I thought I'd bring
the dinner to him.

50:27.463 --> 50:30.134
-Oh, I'm sorry. I'm Grant.

50:30.169 --> 50:32.961
I'm, uh --
I'm one of the editors here.

50:32.996 --> 50:35.502
You -- You look very familiar.

50:35.537 --> 50:39.110
-I don't believe we've met.
I live next door to David.

50:39.145 --> 50:40.474
-Robert!
-Yes.

50:40.509 --> 50:43.345
-Yes. Well, we have met.
I -- I own the house.

50:43.380 --> 50:45.611
-Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't recognize you.

50:45.646 --> 50:50.352
-Yeah. Well, um, David left
about a half an hour ago.

50:50.387 --> 50:52.156
He said he was going to go down
to Main Street,

50:52.191 --> 50:56.160
get some sushi, and then,
uh, come back, finish up.

50:56.195 --> 51:00.054
But, uh, I mean, it --
it smells nice.

51:01.431 --> 51:04.399
-Why don't you enjoy it,
while it's warm?

51:04.434 --> 51:07.061
-Oh, well,
that's very sweet of you.

51:07.096 --> 51:09.833
-It's my pleasure, Grant.

51:12.541 --> 51:16.840
♪♪

51:18.448 --> 51:21.746
-So did you always know
you wanted to be a writer?

51:21.781 --> 51:24.386
-Uh, yeah, sort of.

51:24.421 --> 51:27.686
My mother used to say
she always knew when I was a kid

51:27.721 --> 51:31.162
because I'd have all these
random questions, you know?

51:31.197 --> 51:33.692
Like, here's one --

51:33.727 --> 51:36.398
Why is there a "D"
in "fridge" --

51:36.433 --> 51:38.202
think about it...
-Mm-hmm.

51:38.237 --> 51:41.205
-...and not "refrigerator"

51:41.240 --> 51:50.742
♪♪

51:50.777 --> 51:59.916
♪♪

51:59.951 --> 52:02.721
-So I didn't ask you --
what do you do for a living?

52:02.756 --> 52:05.724
-Mm. Graphic designer.

52:05.759 --> 52:07.891
-Wow, very cool.

52:07.926 --> 52:11.301
-It's good because I can work
from anywhere,

52:11.336 --> 52:15.063
but London is home.

52:15.098 --> 52:17.736
-So you married?

52:17.771 --> 52:19.738
-No.

52:19.773 --> 52:21.102
Almost.

52:21.137 --> 52:26.547
We were together six years,
but it just didn't work out.

52:26.582 --> 52:28.582
You?

52:28.617 --> 52:32.190
-On the mend
from a recent split.

52:33.787 --> 52:36.051
-Sorry to hear that.

52:36.086 --> 52:41.925
♪♪

52:41.960 --> 52:45.269
Hey, last piece is yours.

52:45.304 --> 52:47.799
-No, it's yours. I insist.

52:47.834 --> 52:51.132
♪♪

52:51.167 --> 52:53.002
-I insist.

52:59.318 --> 53:00.713
Sorry.

53:02.145 --> 53:03.287
Mm-hmm.

53:05.181 --> 53:08.182
Well, thanks for a nice evening.

53:08.217 --> 53:10.954
-Yeah. You're welcome.
-I needed that.

53:10.989 --> 53:14.397
-What the fuck?

53:15.961 --> 53:17.697
-Shit.

53:17.732 --> 53:20.832
-Who would do something
like this?

53:20.867 --> 53:27.311
♪♪

53:27.346 --> 53:28.807
I'm -- I'm sorry.

53:28.842 --> 53:30.677
Uh...

53:32.010 --> 53:33.812
Can I give you a ride home?

53:33.847 --> 53:38.685
-It's okay. I'm only like
a five-minute walk from here.

53:41.019 --> 53:43.360
Thanks.

53:46.024 --> 53:48.024
-Mm-hmm.

53:48.059 --> 53:50.895
Have a good night.
-You, too.

53:53.702 --> 53:55.669
-Great.

53:57.035 --> 53:58.705
Fuck me.

54:14.052 --> 54:20.991
♪♪

54:21.026 --> 54:27.932
♪♪

54:29.232 --> 54:38.074
♪♪

54:41.750 --> 54:45.950
♪♪

54:58.327 --> 55:04.705
♪♪

55:04.740 --> 55:10.645
♪♪

55:10.680 --> 55:14.583
-Hey, Robert, it's, uh
it's David again.

55:14.618 --> 55:16.552
Been trying to reach you

55:16.587 --> 55:19.621
Just give me a call
when you get this.

55:19.656 --> 55:20.919
Bye.

55:28.159 --> 55:29.829
Hi.

55:29.864 --> 55:31.633
-Uh, Vanessa. Hi.

55:33.769 --> 55:36.836
-I'm sorry for i-intruding.

55:36.871 --> 55:42.072
I went to your office,
and they said you were here.

55:42.107 --> 55:45.449
I wanted to give you these
to say thank you

55:45.484 --> 55:49.618
for being so helpful,
for listening to me.

55:50.885 --> 55:55.019
-Thank you.
Uh, you really sh-shouldn't --

55:55.054 --> 55:57.494
-Please.

55:58.827 --> 56:00.794
-Okay.

56:03.502 --> 56:06.360
-Can I come in?

56:11.477 --> 56:15.710
Janine and I,
we weren't really speaking.

56:15.745 --> 56:22.453
We got into this huge fight
in Greece last summer.

56:22.488 --> 56:25.687
And she left to come here.

56:27.526 --> 56:30.527
Just so stupid.

56:33.895 --> 56:39.030
I just wish I'd done more
to resolve things.

56:39.065 --> 56:41.703
I feel so guilty.

56:44.169 --> 56:46.543
And I miss her.

56:46.578 --> 56:49.139
I really miss her.

56:49.174 --> 56:51.680
God.

56:53.915 --> 56:56.553
I'm -- I'm sorry.

56:57.589 --> 56:59.985
-No, it's okay.

57:05.564 --> 57:13.867
♪♪

57:13.902 --> 57:16.133
-Okay.

57:17.235 --> 57:20.368
Hey, I didn't know
if you wanted some --

57:20.403 --> 57:29.520
♪♪

57:29.555 --> 57:38.859
♪♪

57:38.894 --> 57:43.457
♪♪

57:47.771 --> 57:51.905
-So cheerful, bright.

57:51.940 --> 57:54.545
Beautiful.

57:57.341 --> 57:59.715
Much too early to be called way.

57:59.750 --> 58:03.048
-She was the best chef,

58:03.083 --> 58:05.589
the best colleague,

58:05.624 --> 58:08.757
the kindest person at all.

58:08.792 --> 58:12.288
-May she...rest in peace

58:12.323 --> 58:18.459
and...have freedom...forever.

58:18.494 --> 58:21.671
-Janine and I had been
through so much.

58:23.136 --> 58:25.642
We were always there
for each other.

58:25.677 --> 58:29.272
It's amazing to see
that she found her tribe

58:29.307 --> 58:31.780
in such a beautiful place.

58:31.815 --> 58:33.782
To Janine.
-To Janine.

58:33.817 --> 58:35.784
-To Janine.
-To Janine.

58:35.819 --> 58:38.853
-I'm so sorry, Vanessa.

58:38.888 --> 58:47.290
♪♪

58:47.325 --> 58:49.457
-Hi. Thank you for coming.

58:49.492 --> 58:52.163
-I'm sorry for your loss.

58:52.198 --> 58:58.367
♪♪

59:00.008 --> 59:01.975
-Where were you?

59:04.210 --> 59:06.980
-What?
-Were you at the memorial?

59:07.015 --> 59:10.115
-Yeah, I had to cover it
for work.

59:10.150 --> 59:13.151
-Why was Vanessa Rafael
at your house last night?

59:15.518 --> 59:17.353
-Are you spying on me now?

59:17.388 --> 59:20.389
-Her Uber turned around
in my driveway and woke me up.

59:20.424 --> 59:23.293
Have you read this?

59:23.328 --> 59:25.163
-David!

59:25.198 --> 59:29.200
The sister, David.
The bloody woman is dead!

59:29.235 --> 59:32.005
And you want to go play therapy
with the sister.

59:32.040 --> 59:34.502
What are you trying to be,
David?

59:34.537 --> 59:37.076
Her rock?

59:37.111 --> 59:39.210
Look...

59:41.720 --> 59:45.018
All I've ever asked of you
is your loyalty.

59:45.053 --> 59:46.855
I need to know I can count --

59:46.890 --> 59:49.924
-I'm not going to tell her
a damn thing.

59:49.959 --> 59:51.695
Trust me.

59:55.932 --> 59:58.768
Eventually, she finds out
everything.

59:59.969 --> 1:00:02.530
Women always do, David.

1:00:02.565 --> 1:00:05.203
Then what?

1:00:10.078 --> 1:00:14.080
♪♪

1:00:16.381 --> 1:00:25.553
♪♪

1:00:25.588 --> 1:00:34.738
♪♪

1:00:34.773 --> 1:00:43.307
♪♪

1:00:43.342 --> 1:00:44.880
-Well, that's about it, then,
I guess.

1:00:44.915 --> 1:00:48.576
Um, no questions,
uh, have a good weekend.

1:00:48.611 --> 1:00:50.754
-Have a nice weekend.
-Thank you. Bye.

1:00:58.687 --> 1:01:01.930
-Uh, Henry, could I speak
to you a second?

1:01:01.965 --> 1:01:04.592
How's David doing?

1:01:04.627 --> 1:01:08.068
-Well, actually, he missed
a couple of deadlines.

1:01:08.103 --> 1:01:09.597
-A couple?

1:01:26.517 --> 1:01:29.122
-Hey. How you doing?

1:01:29.157 --> 1:01:33.995
-Yeah, you know, I'm just,
uh, really swamped at work.

1:01:35.163 --> 1:01:38.769
-You haven't returned
any of my calls.

1:01:38.804 --> 1:01:41.739
Are you sure you're okay?

1:01:44.876 --> 1:01:48.812
-I don't think we should do this
anymore, Vanessa.

1:01:57.746 --> 1:02:00.890
-We met because of Janine.

1:02:00.925 --> 1:02:04.157
Don't you think some good
can come of that,

1:02:04.192 --> 1:02:08.326
some light
after all this darkness?

1:02:08.361 --> 1:02:11.395
Could be a chance
for both of us.

1:02:11.430 --> 1:02:21.075
♪♪

1:02:21.110 --> 1:02:30.546
♪♪

1:02:30.581 --> 1:02:40.226
♪♪

1:02:40.261 --> 1:02:49.697
♪♪

1:02:49.732 --> 1:02:57.342
♪♪

1:03:00.413 --> 1:03:02.215
-Yeah? Grant here.

1:03:02.250 --> 1:03:04.217
-Hello. This is Officer Pavlows.

1:03:04.252 --> 1:03:06.582
I'm calling about
your stolen car,

1:03:06.617 --> 1:03:09.684
a 1984 BMW.

1:03:09.719 --> 1:03:11.554
-My stolen car?

1:03:11.589 --> 1:03:20.728
♪♪

1:03:20.763 --> 1:03:29.880
♪♪

1:03:32.478 --> 1:03:38.416
♪♪

1:03:47.328 --> 1:03:49.493
-David?!

1:04:24.728 --> 1:04:26.970
-Hey, there.

1:04:27.005 --> 1:04:36.980
♪♪

1:04:37.015 --> 1:04:46.990
♪♪

1:04:47.025 --> 1:04:57.000
♪♪

1:04:57.035 --> 1:05:07.010
♪♪

1:05:07.045 --> 1:05:17.218
♪♪

1:05:17.253 --> 1:05:19.220
-So nice.

1:05:19.255 --> 1:05:21.684
-Mm-hmm.

1:05:21.719 --> 1:05:24.390
-I'll go get the kayaks.
-Okay.

1:05:36.635 --> 1:05:39.702
-Thank you very much.
-Take care. Have fun.

1:05:41.145 --> 1:05:42.705
-There's a really nice point
to stop

1:05:42.740 --> 1:05:44.575
if you want to stop
for a romantic lunch,

1:05:44.610 --> 1:05:47.215
hang out and have a drink. Yeah.
-Cool.

1:05:47.250 --> 1:05:49.415
-Other than that,
the lake is beautiful.

1:05:49.450 --> 1:05:52.220
-Thanks.
-What are you doing here?

1:05:52.255 --> 1:05:54.519
-You know each other?
-Yes.

1:05:54.554 --> 1:05:56.917
How do you know each other?
-This is Vanessa.

1:05:56.952 --> 1:05:58.886
We're friends from work.

1:05:58.921 --> 1:06:01.262
Vanessa, this is my neighbor.

1:06:01.297 --> 1:06:03.198
-Oh, I'd like to think
I'm a little bit more than that.

1:06:03.233 --> 1:06:06.399
I'm his friend -- Robert.
Pleasure to meet you.

1:06:06.434 --> 1:06:09.369
-Have we met?
-Oh, I think I'd remember.

1:06:09.404 --> 1:06:12.075
-I think our kayaks are ready.

1:06:12.110 --> 1:06:14.209
-Okay. Nice to meet you.

1:06:14.244 --> 1:06:17.212
-And you, Vanessa.

1:06:17.247 --> 1:06:19.907
-What the fuck
are you doing here?

1:06:19.942 --> 1:06:22.118
-Kayaking.

1:06:30.018 --> 1:06:32.656
There you are.

1:06:32.691 --> 1:06:34.889
What a beautiful day.

1:06:34.924 --> 1:06:37.430
Not too hot, not too humid.

1:06:37.465 --> 1:06:39.960
-I somehow imagined this
differently.

1:06:39.995 --> 1:06:42.930
-Hey, Robert, uh, do you mind

1:06:42.965 --> 1:06:45.273
giving us
a little bit of privacy?

1:06:45.308 --> 1:06:48.078
-I'll find a good spot,
and I'll leave you two alone.

1:06:48.113 --> 1:06:50.773
By the way, special occasion?

1:06:50.808 --> 1:06:55.415
-My sister and I used to do this
trick before she passed away.

1:06:55.450 --> 1:06:58.187
We thought we'd do it
to celebrate her.

1:06:58.222 --> 1:07:01.454
-God, that's awful.
I'm so sorry. What happened?

1:07:03.722 --> 1:07:05.491
-She was hit by a car.

1:07:05.526 --> 1:07:07.295
-A car?

1:07:07.330 --> 1:07:09.924
That's not the girl
in the newspaper?

1:07:09.959 --> 1:07:11.299
-Robert.

1:07:11.334 --> 1:07:12.630
-They still haven't
caught him, right?

1:07:12.665 --> 1:07:15.798
-Robert, please. Please.
-That man's a pig.

1:07:15.833 --> 1:07:18.603
I can't believe that bastard.
Leave a beautiful girl like that

1:07:18.638 --> 1:07:21.408
dying in the street
like an animal.

1:07:22.873 --> 1:07:24.213
Vanessa! Vanessa!
-Vanessa!

1:07:24.248 --> 1:07:26.677
-I'm sorry! I'm so sorry.

1:07:28.076 --> 1:07:30.516
-Vanessa! Robert!

1:07:33.224 --> 1:07:35.158
Son of a bitch.

1:07:35.193 --> 1:07:44.398
♪♪

1:07:44.433 --> 1:07:53.242
♪♪

1:07:53.277 --> 1:07:55.673
Motherfucker.

1:07:55.708 --> 1:08:01.547
♪♪

1:08:01.582 --> 1:08:03.681
-Aah!

1:08:03.716 --> 1:08:13.053
♪♪

1:08:17.862 --> 1:08:22.535
♪♪

1:08:22.570 --> 1:08:24.064
-Robert!

1:08:24.099 --> 1:08:29.905
♪♪

1:08:29.940 --> 1:08:35.779
♪♪

1:08:35.814 --> 1:08:37.847
Oh, my God.

1:08:37.882 --> 1:08:47.824
♪♪

1:08:49.663 --> 1:08:51.025
-David!

1:08:51.060 --> 1:08:52.928
David! Here!

1:08:52.963 --> 1:09:02.938
♪♪

1:09:02.973 --> 1:09:12.948
♪♪

1:09:12.983 --> 1:09:17.117
♪♪

1:09:19.792 --> 1:09:21.561
-I got you.

1:09:21.596 --> 1:09:23.365
I got you.

1:09:26.667 --> 1:09:28.062
Hey.

1:09:28.097 --> 1:09:29.437
-Hey.

1:09:29.472 --> 1:09:31.934
-Here you go.
-Thanks.

1:09:34.202 --> 1:09:36.708
How you doing? You okay?

1:09:37.843 --> 1:09:39.777
-Thanks.

1:09:41.880 --> 1:09:44.078
I saw --

1:09:44.113 --> 1:09:47.114
I thought I saw --

1:09:47.149 --> 1:09:49.787
I thought Robert --

1:09:51.857 --> 1:09:53.626
-Robert what?

1:09:56.862 --> 1:09:59.126
-Nothing.

1:09:59.161 --> 1:10:02.096
Doesn't matter.

1:10:02.131 --> 1:10:04.736
I'm just glad it's over.

1:10:18.213 --> 1:10:20.884
How is she? Is she alright?

1:10:20.919 --> 1:10:23.623
-She -- She almost drowned,
Robert.

1:10:23.658 --> 1:10:25.328
What the hell is wrong with you?

1:10:25.363 --> 1:10:26.626
-I have no idea what
you're talking about.

1:10:26.661 --> 1:10:28.056
-You know exactly
what I'm talking about.

1:10:28.091 --> 1:10:30.630
Do you think this is
some kind of game, huh?

1:10:30.665 --> 1:10:32.995
You come down here.
You insult her.

1:10:33.030 --> 1:10:34.997
You embarrass me.

1:10:35.032 --> 1:10:37.164
-Insult her?

1:10:37.199 --> 1:10:39.408
Embarrass you?

1:10:39.443 --> 1:10:43.445
You killed her sister.
You're doing the insulting.

1:10:45.383 --> 1:10:48.747
-You know, Robert,
why don't you just leave?

1:10:48.782 --> 1:10:50.584
-Or what?

1:10:53.116 --> 1:10:55.149
-Or what?
-Yeah.

1:10:55.184 --> 1:10:57.393
Or what?

1:10:59.056 --> 1:11:01.892
-I got this under control.

1:11:01.927 --> 1:11:04.400
-I know you do.

1:11:04.435 --> 1:11:06.765
Of course.

1:11:06.800 --> 1:11:08.899
I'm sorry.

1:11:12.905 --> 1:11:22.880
♪♪

1:11:22.915 --> 1:11:32.890
♪♪

1:11:32.925 --> 1:11:35.332
-Mr. Stevens?

1:11:36.500 --> 1:11:38.764
I'm Detective Reine.

1:11:38.799 --> 1:11:41.096
-Yes, I know who you are.
I was at the press conference.

1:11:41.131 --> 1:11:43.439
-Ah. Oh.

1:11:43.474 --> 1:11:46.035
What a coincidence.

1:11:46.070 --> 1:11:48.235
How are you?
-Good.

1:11:48.270 --> 1:11:50.270
Is there news about my sister?

1:11:50.305 --> 1:11:52.481
-No. Sorry.

1:11:52.516 --> 1:11:55.682
Actually, we are here
to talk with Mr. Stevens.

1:11:58.951 --> 1:12:00.588
-Please have a seat.
-Oh, thank you.

1:12:00.623 --> 1:12:01.919
-Can I get you
something to drink?

1:12:01.954 --> 1:12:04.823
-No. Actually, the reason
we are here

1:12:04.858 --> 1:12:08.431
is you reported your car stolen,
Mr. Stevens.

1:12:08.466 --> 1:12:11.500
-Yes. Well, technically,
it's not my car.
-Mm.

1:12:11.535 --> 1:12:14.437
We know. Our officer
tried to confirm the owner,

1:12:14.472 --> 1:12:16.472
but he hasn't returned the call.

1:12:16.507 --> 1:12:20.608
-I think he's on a getaway with
some friends for the weekend,

1:12:20.643 --> 1:12:22.445
yeah.
-Huh.

1:12:22.480 --> 1:12:24.612
-You reported the theft
on Saturday,

1:12:24.647 --> 1:12:26.779
after the hit-and-run
last week, yeah?

1:12:26.814 --> 1:12:29.617
-Yeah, on Saturday.
It might have been Friday.

1:12:29.652 --> 1:12:33.313
-Small details, right?
-I think it was Saturday, yes.

1:12:33.348 --> 1:12:36.283
-Let me ask you something.

1:12:36.318 --> 1:12:39.759
-Thursday night, where were you?

1:12:39.794 --> 1:12:43.026
-Thursday night?
-Yeah.

1:12:43.061 --> 1:12:44.500
-Um...

1:12:44.535 --> 1:12:46.700
Teritorija bar.

1:12:46.735 --> 1:12:49.296
-Was Ms. Rafael there, as well?

1:12:49.331 --> 1:12:53.135
-No. No, we...met
at your briefing.

1:12:53.170 --> 1:12:55.808
-No, I mean,<i> Janine</i> Rafael.

1:12:56.547 --> 1:12:59.977
-I'm sorry. Uh, what --
what is this about?

1:13:00.012 --> 1:13:02.650
I don't understand.
-Ms. Rafael's phone records.

1:13:02.685 --> 1:13:06.984
You called her that night
at, uh -- at- 28?

1:13:07.019 --> 1:13:09.690
-That must be a mistake.

1:13:12.893 --> 1:13:14.827
I did make a call that night
at the bar.

1:13:14.862 --> 1:13:18.996
There was a woman, and she wrote
on my arm, and then she left.

1:13:19.031 --> 1:13:21.834
God, I'm -- I didn't know
that was her.

1:13:21.869 --> 1:13:24.364
-How long were you at the bar?

1:13:24.399 --> 1:13:27.136
-Uh, not very long.

1:13:27.171 --> 1:13:30.073
Quarter past twelve.
I took the tram home.

1:13:31.340 --> 1:13:33.879
-Can anyone testify to that?

1:13:37.555 --> 1:13:43.119
Mr. Stevens,
can anyone testify to that?

1:13:45.057 --> 1:13:47.563
Yes.

1:13:47.598 --> 1:13:50.863
Robert, my neighbor,
he was with me all night.

1:13:50.898 --> 1:13:52.667
-Okay.

1:13:52.702 --> 1:13:55.835
So we'll have a little chat
with him.

1:13:55.870 --> 1:14:05.845
♪♪

1:14:05.880 --> 1:14:15.921
♪♪

1:14:20.488 --> 1:14:22.796
-You knew my sister.

1:14:22.831 --> 1:14:24.259
-I guess I did,
but it was brief.

1:14:24.294 --> 1:14:25.700
I didn't even realize.

1:14:25.735 --> 1:14:28.131
-Well, you knew her well enough
to call her.

1:14:34.172 --> 1:14:35.435
-Why didn't you tell me?

1:14:35.470 --> 1:14:38.746
-Because I didn't realize
until just now.

1:14:38.781 --> 1:14:41.408
-And the car missing?

1:14:41.443 --> 1:14:43.883
That doesn't seem odd to you?

1:14:43.918 --> 1:14:46.589
-That was stolen from work.
You knew that.

1:14:46.624 --> 1:14:48.250
-Well,
it's a fucking coincidence.

1:14:48.285 --> 1:14:50.923
-What do you want me to say?

1:14:50.958 --> 1:14:54.762
-I want you
to tell me the truth.

1:14:54.797 --> 1:14:57.996
-Did you know my sister?

1:15:01.199 --> 1:15:03.639
I -- I knew her.

1:15:03.674 --> 1:15:06.609
But I didn't realize I did.

1:15:06.644 --> 1:15:09.436
What does that change?

1:15:09.471 --> 1:15:12.010
-Everything.

1:15:17.314 --> 1:15:26.453
♪♪

1:15:29.964 --> 1:15:33.163
♪♪

1:15:36.641 --> 1:15:38.498
-What did you tell them?

1:15:38.533 --> 1:15:40.874
-The truth.

1:15:43.472 --> 1:15:45.879
We took a tram at midnight.

1:15:45.914 --> 1:15:48.112
-Took a tram at midnight.

1:15:48.147 --> 1:15:50.048
-Okay?

1:15:50.083 --> 1:15:52.050
Come in.

1:15:55.517 --> 1:15:57.627
This has to stop.

1:15:57.662 --> 1:16:00.157
-What has to stop?

1:16:00.192 --> 1:16:02.555
-You at the wheel.

1:16:08.937 --> 1:16:11.971
You think you're the only one
with something to lose here?

1:16:12.006 --> 1:16:14.677
-They don't have
anything on us, right?

1:16:14.712 --> 1:16:17.207
They don't have a car.

1:16:17.242 --> 1:16:19.506
They don't have a witness.

1:16:19.541 --> 1:16:21.211
-No.

1:16:21.246 --> 1:16:25.754
Sleeping with the dead girl's
sister puts us at risk.

1:16:27.054 --> 1:16:30.517
You have to deal with it...

1:16:30.552 --> 1:16:32.189
now.

1:16:32.224 --> 1:16:38.360
♪♪

1:16:38.395 --> 1:16:44.498
♪♪

1:16:47.041 --> 1:16:55.047
♪♪

1:16:55.082 --> 1:16:58.116
-What could you possibly
have to say to me?

1:16:59.988 --> 1:17:01.383
-I...

1:17:01.418 --> 1:17:04.287
-What, you're going to
make something up?

1:17:04.322 --> 1:17:06.586
I don't think so.

1:17:06.621 --> 1:17:11.294
♪♪

1:17:12.968 --> 1:17:16.068
<i>-Ludza are the best</i>
<i>fishing grounds in the world.</i>

1:17:16.103 --> 1:17:18.367
<i>Throughout the year,</i>
<i>from March to October,</i>

1:17:18.402 --> 1:17:21.634
<i>fish can be found</i>
<i>in more than 50 lakes.</i>

1:17:21.669 --> 1:17:27.376
♪♪

1:17:27.411 --> 1:17:32.887
♪♪

1:17:32.922 --> 1:17:35.791
-It's over. Are you satisfied?

1:17:35.826 --> 1:17:38.761
-She'll turn on you.

1:17:38.796 --> 1:17:41.555
She'll ruin your life.

1:17:41.590 --> 1:17:43.766
You can't trust anyone, David.

1:17:45.198 --> 1:17:54.634
♪♪

1:17:57.177 --> 1:18:05.788
♪♪

1:18:18.165 --> 1:18:19.692
♪♪

1:18:19.727 --> 1:18:21.430
-Hi.
-Hi.

1:18:21.465 --> 1:18:24.037
-Vodka martini, please.
